<h1>TikTok filters but without Lightroom</h1>
<p>Experimental filters in the browser using ffmpeg with wasm.</p>
<h3>Privacy notice</h3>
<p>Nothing leaves your device! Isn't that neat.</p>
<h3>Raw images!</h3>
<p>
  This tool supports raw images from many cameras. Try uploading one!
</p>

<button id="ffmpeg-load">Load ffmpeg (~32 MB)</button>

<div id="ffmpeg-loaded" style="display:none;">
  <input
    type="file"
    id="ffmpeg-file"
    accept="image/*,.3fr,.ari,.arw,.bay,.braw,.crw,.cr2,.cr3,.cap,.data,.dcs,.dcr,.dng,.drf,.eip,.erf,.fff,.gpr,.iiq,.k25,.kdc,.mdc,.mef,.mos,.mrw,.nef,.nrw,.obm,.orf,.pef,.ptx,.pxn,.r3d,.raf,.raw,.rwl,.rw2,.rwz,.sr2,.srf,.srw,.tif,.x3f"
  >
  <div style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
    <label for="ffmpeg-filters">Filters</label>
    <select
      id="ffmpeg-filters"
      multiple
      size="5"
      style="display:block;min-width:18rem;max-width:100%;margin-top:0.25rem;"
    >
      <option value="retro-1">Retro 1</option>
      <option value="film">Film</option>
      <option value="disposable-camera">Disposable Camera</option>
      <option value="cyberpunk">Cyberpunk</option>
    </select>
  </div>
  <div id="ffmpeg-controls"></div>
  <button id="ffmpeg-apply" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Apply filters</button>
  <div style="margin-top:1rem;">
    <img id="ffmpeg-image" alt="Filtered output" style="display:none;max-width:100%;height:auto;">
    <div style="margin-top:0.5rem;">
      <a id="ffmpeg-download" style="display:none;" href="#">Download</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p id="ffmpeg-message"></p>
</div>

<script type="module" src="/js/filters.js"></script>

<style>
  #map {
    display: none !important;
  }
</style>
